title: Prep football: Rocori tops Little Falls, advances
text:
Prep football: Rocori tops Little Falls, advances Tom Elliott , telliott@stcloudtimes.com 11:42 p.m. CDT October 13, 2015 Buy Photo Rocori's Alex Anderson pulls in a pass and takes it past Little Falls' Hunter Swanson on a 50-yard touchdown run in the first half Tuesday in Cold Spring. (Photo: Jason Wachter, jwachter@stcloudtimes.com) Buy Photo 
COLD SPRING — Austin Overman couldn’t put his finger on it. But for whatever reason, the Rocori Spartans got off to a slow start Tuesday night. 
“We were flat,” the Rocori senior linebacker said. “It’s been a problem for us this year.” 
Little Falls scored first and then Rocori woke up. 
The Spartans beat the Flyers 27-14 in the Section 8-4A high school football playoff game Virant Memorial Field. 
“It took us a while to get going,” Rocori junior quarterback Connor Schoborg said. “We needed to couple first downs before we were into it.” Buy Photo Rocori quarterback Connor Schoborg rolls out to throw a pass against Little Falls in the first half. Rocori’s first three drives went nowhere: two three-and-outs and then an interception by the Flyers’ Thomas Miller that helped set up Little Falls’ first TD. Landon Bjorge caught an eight-yard scoring pass from Braden Backowski and Wyatt Nelson’s kick made it 7-0. 
“I’m proud of our boys,” Little Falls head coach Joe Bartos said. “They played their butts off. 
“They gave a perfect effort and they’re great young men. I’m proud to be their football coach.” 
Things got going for Rocori (6-3) with two second-quarter touchdowns. Their 13-7 lead turned into a 27-7 advantage in the third quarter. 
And that was enough to send the third-seeded Spartans into the section semifinals. They play at 6 p.m. Saturday at second-seeded Detroit Lakes (7-1). 
“We definitely did good in the second half,” said Rocori senior linebacker Ryan Vigil. “We had some turnovers and we we got two touchdowns.” 
Gunnar Feldhege picked off an errant Flyer pass and the Spartans’ offense took over on the Little Falls 21. Five plays later, Schoborg found Nick Skluzacek in the end zone for a 9-yard TD. 
The Spartans then forced another turnover. Dominic Theis recovered a fumble after a hard hit by Ethan Braun. Rocori’s drive stalled in the red zone, but it gave the Spartans good field position when the Flyers were forced to punt. 
On their next possession, Tommy Wieber scored on a three-yard TD run and Rocori had a 20-point lead. Buy Photo 
Rocori's Nick Warne fights the ball over the goal line past Little Falls' Austin Erdmann to score in the first half Tuesday in Cold Spring. (Photo: Jason Wachter, jwachter@stcloudtimes.com) 
“I thought Little Falls played a good game,” Rocori head coach Mike Rowe said of the sixth-seeded Flyers. “And we made some big plays when we needed to.” 
Rocori ran 83 plays for 370 yards. Nick Warne had 20 carries for 98 yards and a touchdown. Schoborg completed 17 of 31 passes for 202 yards and two TDs. 
One touchdown was a 50-yarder to Alec Anderson. The other was to Skluzacek. 
For Little Falls, Bjorge wound up with eight receptions for 81 yards and two TDs. 
“Solid,” was Bartos’ description of the Spartans. “They’re a decent football team and very classy. 
“They should be very tough the rest of the playoffs.
